      "text": "A newly released video shows two men attacking a 77-year-old man who was walking down the street in downtown Seattle last month.\n\nThe incident was captured by the city's Real Time Crime Center surveillance cameras, which monitor public areas that have been identified as crime hot spots.\n\nIn the video, the victim is seen walking slowly southbound on Third Avenue, approaching a pharmacy at the corner of Pike Street.\n\nWithout any prior interaction, two men shove the man to the ground and punch him, the video shows. They are then seen walking away from the man, who is left hunched over on the ground as bystanders walk past him. None of the witnesses to the attack approached or offered assistance to the man as he remained on the ground.\n\nFull story here: https://t.co/G2MnAFhD6f\n\n#komo #komo4 #komonews #komo4news #seattle #washington",
